### **Mindfulness Audio Style Guide**

**1. Core Colors**
```css
:root {
  --warm-beige: #E8E2DA;
  --sage-green: #B9C2A8;
  --slate-blue: #A2ADB8;
  --dusty-rose: #D8B4A0;
  --charcoal-grey: #444444;
  --soft-grey: #888888;
}
```

**2. Typography**
```css
body {
  font-family: 'Lato', 'Alegreya Sans', sans-serif;
  color: var(--charcoal-grey);
  background-color: var(--warm-beige);
  line-height: 1.6;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}
h1 {
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: 2.6em;
  color: var(--sage-green);
}
h2 {
  font-weight: 400;
  font-size: 1.8em;
  color: var(--slate-blue);
}
footer, .credits {
  font-weight: 300;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  color: var(--soft-grey);
}
```

**3. Layout Ratios**
- **Margins:** 10 % outer padding / top spacing before title 40 % of art height.  
- **Title block:** center aligned; subtitle offset 5 % lower.  
- **Imagery area:** lower 50 % of canvas with 20–30 % translucent overlay using any accent tone.  
- **Footer bar:** bottom 5 %, text scaled 1.5–2 % of width.

**4. Visual Elements**
- Rounded corners (border-radius 4–6 px) for thumbnails and buttons.  
- Subtle box‑shadow using `rgba(68,68,68,0.15)` for soft depth.  
- Avoid stark borders or high‑saturation gradients.

**5. Accessibility**
- Minimum contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for subtitle text.  
- Maintain breathable spacing; never crowd edges.

**6. Attribution / Transparency Note**
> *Mindfulness / Relaxation Audio • © 2024 [Your Name]*  
> This material is for general wellness and mindful practice, not therapy or medical treatment.

